00:04:44.590 --> 00:04:51.980
Next, Mr Philip Glass is a
world-renowned composer-pianist

00:04:51.980 --> 00:04:55.870
whose work spans generations.

00:04:55.870 --> 00:05:01.270
There is no doubt
Philip Glass has

00:05:01.270 --> 00:05:07.090
had a transforming presence in
our musical and intellectual

00:05:07.090 --> 00:05:08.860
lives.

00:05:08.860 --> 00:05:12.390
In the last 25
years alone, Glass

00:05:12.390 --> 00:05:15.190
has composed more
than 20 operas,

00:05:15.190 --> 00:05:18.690
eight symphonies,
two piano concertos,

00:05:18.690 --> 00:05:24.950
soundtracks to films, and still
maintains his expansive solo

00:05:24.950 --> 00:05:30.240
creations on both
piano and organ.

00:05:30.240 --> 00:05:34.120
Philip grew up in Baltimore,
studied at Juilliard,

00:05:34.120 --> 00:05:38.270
and moved to Europe, where he
trained with Nadia Boulanger

00:05:38.270 --> 00:05:42.005
and worked closely with
the composer Ravi Shankar.

00:05:45.540 --> 00:05:49.620
Philip Glass is best known
for his repetitive structures

00:05:49.620 --> 00:05:55.095
in music, and has developed
what some call minimalist music.

00:05:58.430 --> 00:06:00.960
When he returned to New
York in the late 60s,

00:06:00.960 --> 00:06:03.710
he formed the Philip
Glass Ensemble,

00:06:03.710 --> 00:06:07.210
and still performs with
that group to date.

00:06:07.210 --> 00:06:10.090
This November, Philip
Glass turns 80,

00:06:10.090 --> 00:06:12.880
and he's still going strong.

00:06:12.880 --> 00:06:17.990
He has collaborated with Paul
Simon, Yo Yo Ma, to name a few.

00:06:17.990 --> 00:06:22.120
And he still presents lectures
and performs solo keyboard

00:06:22.120 --> 00:06:24.600
concerts around the world.

00:06:24.600 --> 00:06:29.490
In 2011, he founded the
Philip Glass Center-- home

00:06:29.490 --> 00:06:33.180
for artists, scientists,
and conservatists

00:06:33.180 --> 00:06:38.250
to collaborate and produce a
culture of our renewal time.

00:06:38.250 --> 00:06:41.910
Please welcome to the
stage Mr Philip Glass.

